properties.sfomuseum:description: Airmail flight cover issued by Pan American World Airways commemorating first day of issue for Samoan 20-sene airmail stamp featuring image of PAA “Samoan Clipper” and Western Samoa internal air service between Apia on Upolu and Assau on Savai’i; red circular stamp “Special airmail via Pan - Am / Pago to U.S.A.”; postmarked July 27, 1970 in Apia, Western Samoa; backstamp: July 31, 1970 in San Francisco; envelope addressed to H. G. Gulbransen.a. Envelopeb. Typed enclosure by W. L. Rolph, Director - Sales, Auckland, New Zealand.
